title: Urbanization in Canada 2018
summary: In general Share of urban population has stayed the same over the Year.
Share of urban population is slightly increasing from 2009 to 2011.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2009 and 2010.
Maximum Share of urban population, about 81.1 was reported at Year 2011
The lowest Share of urban population, of value 80.76 was reported at Year 2009
